### 5. If you’re intentionally time traveling / restarting

Mastra also has:

- `run.restart()` – restarts from the last active step (but **re-executes** from there)  
- `run.timeTravel()` – replays from any step based on snapshots

If you accidentally call these instead of `resume()`, you’ll also see “start over” behavior.

Reference: https://mastra.ai/docs/workflows/overview (see “Time travel & restart” via links to Run methods)

