## 4. Using filters with `createVectorQueryTool` (agents)

If you’re letting an agent decide filters via the Vector Query Tool, you can still enforce a base filter (e.g. always restrict to a particular source or date window) by passing it into the tool’s configuration or merging it before query execution.

Example pattern:

```ts
import { createVectorQueryTool } from "@mastra/rag";

const vectorQueryTool = createVectorQueryTool({
  vectorStoreName: "postgres",
  indexName: "myCollection",
  model: new ModelRouterEmbeddingModel("openai/text-embedding-3-small"),
});

// Then in your own wrapper around the tool:
const baseFilter = {
  source: "docs/manual.pdf",
  createdAt: { $gte: "2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z" },
};

// When you construct the tool input, merge the agent’s filter with baseFilter
// (exact merge logic depends on how you wire the tool, but conceptually it’s:
//
// filter = { $and: [baseFilter, agentFilter] }
//
//)
```

