## 3. Expose your Mastra app as an MCP server (`MCPServer`)

### 3.1 Define a tool and agent

`src/mastra/tools/test-tool.ts`:

```ts
import { createTool } from "@mastra/core/tools";
import { z } from "zod";

export const testTool = createTool({
  id: "getGreeting",
  description: "Returns a greeting for a given name",
  inputSchema: z.object({
    name: z.string().describe("Name to greet"),
  }),
  execute: async ({ name }) => {
    return `Hello, ${name}!`;
  },
});
```

`src/mastra/agents/test-agent.ts`:

```ts
