You can do this in Mastra by creating a **composite voice** that uses:

- OpenAI (Whisper) for **speech-to-text (STT)**
- ElevenLabs for **text-to-speech (TTS)**

and then attaching that composite voice to an `Agent`.

Below is a minimal, end‑to‑end setup.

---

## 1. Install required packages

```bash
pnpm add @mastra/core @mastra/core@latest \
  @mastra/voice-openai @mastra/voice-elevenlabs \
  @mastra/node-audio
```

If you want to use the AI SDK integration instead of Mastra voice providers, see step 4.

Set env variables:

```bash
export OPENAI_API_KEY=your-openai-key
export ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=your-elevenlabs-key
```

---

## 2. Create a composite voice: OpenAI STT + ElevenLabs TTS

```ts
// src/voiceAgent.ts
import { Agent } from "@mastra/core/agent";
import { CompositeVoice } from "@mastra/core/voice";
import { OpenAIVoice } from "@mastra/voice-openai";
import { ElevenLabsVoice } from "@mastra/voice-elevenlabs";

const voice = new CompositeVoice({
  // Input side: OpenAI Whisper for STT
  input: new OpenAIVoice({
    listeningModel: {
      name: "whisper-1",
      apiKey: process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY,
    },
  }),
  // Output side: ElevenLabs for TTS
  output: new ElevenLabsVoice({
    speechModel: {
      name: "eleven_multilingual_v2",
      apiKey: process.env.ELEVENLABS_API_KEY,
    },
    // Optional default voice
    speaker: "9BWtsMINqrJLrRacOk9x", // Aria (default in docs)
  }),
});

// Your LLM agent (can still use any model you like, e.g. OpenAI)
export const voiceAgent = new Agent({
  id: "openai-elevenlabs-voice-agent",
  name: "Voice Agent",
  instructions: "You are a helpful conversational assistant.",
  model: "openai/gpt-5.1",
  voice,
});
```

This gives you:

- `voiceAgent.voice.listen(audioStream)` → STT via OpenAI
- `voiceAgent.voice.speak(text)` → TTS via ElevenLabs

---

## 3. Example: listen from mic and respond with speech

This example uses `@mastra/node-audio` to capture microphone audio and play ElevenLabs output.

```ts
// src/runVoiceLoop.ts
import "dotenv/config";
import { getMicrophoneStream, playAudio } from "@mastra/node-audio";
import { voiceAgent } from "./voiceAgent";

async function main() {
  // 1. Capture user speech from mic
  const micStream = getMicrophoneStream();

  console.log("Speak into the microphone...");
  const transcript = await voiceAgent.voice.listen(micStream, {
    filetype: "wav", // or "m4a"/"mp3" depending on your capture setup
  });

  console.log("User said:", transcript);

  // 2. Let the agent think/respond in text
  const { text: reply } = await voiceAgent.generate(transcript);
  console.log("Agent reply:", reply);

  // 3. Speak reply via ElevenLabs
  const audioStream = await voiceAgent.voice.speak(reply, {
    // optional override of default voice for this call
    speaker: "9BWtsMINqrJLrRacOk9x",
  });

  if (audioStream) {
    await playAudio(audioStream);
  }
}

main().catch(console.error);
```

You can also use file-based audio instead of a microphone by passing a `createReadStream(...)` into `voiceAgent.voice.listen`.

---

## 4. Alternative: use AI SDK models directly (no Mastra voice providers)

If you prefer to wire OpenAI + ElevenLabs via the AI SDK (instead of `@mastra/voice-openai` and `@mastra/voice-elevenlabs`), Mastra’s `CompositeVoice` also accepts AI SDK models:

```bash
pnpm add @ai-sdk/openai @ai-sdk/elevenlabs
```

```ts
import { Agent } from "@mastra/core/agent";
import { CompositeVoice } from "@mastra/core/voice";
import { openai } from "@ai-sdk/openai";
import { elevenlabs } from "@ai-sdk/elevenlabs";

const voice = new CompositeVoice({
  // STT: OpenAI Whisper transcription model
  input: openai.transcription("whisper-1"),
  // TTS: ElevenLabs speech model
  output: elevenlabs.speech("eleven_turbo_v2"),
});

export const aiSdkVoiceAgent = new Agent({
  id: "aisdk-voice-agent",
  name: "AI SDK Voice Agent",
  instructions: "You are a helpful assistant with voice capabilities.",
  model: openai("gpt-5.1"),
  voice,
});

// use exactly the same way:
// const transcript = await aiSdkVoiceAgent.voice.listen(micStream);
// const { text } = await aiSdkVoiceAgent.generate(transcript);
// const audio = await aiSdkVoiceAgent.voice.speak(text, { speaker: "Rachel" });
```

This is the most direct mapping to “OpenAI STT + ElevenLabs TTS” and matches the docs’ recommended pattern.

