You can configure `OpenAIRealtimeVoice` to use the `shimmer` speaker and the `gpt-4o-realtime` model by:

1. Passing them in the constructor, or  
2. Updating the config at runtime with `updateConfig`.

Below is a minimal end‑to‑end example for speech‑to‑speech using `gpt-4o-realtime` + `shimmer`.

---

## 1. Install required packages

```bash
pnpm add @mastra/voice-openai-realtime @mastra/node-audio @mastra/core
```

Make sure you have `OPENAI_API_KEY` set in your environment:

```bash
export OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
```

---

## 2. Configure `OpenAIRealtimeVoice` with `gpt-4o-realtime` + `shimmer`

### Simple voice-only setup

```ts
import { OpenAIRealtimeVoice } from "@mastra/voice-openai-realtime";
import { playAudio, getMicrophoneStream } from "@mastra/node-audio";

async function main() {
  // 1. Configure realtime voice with gpt-4o-realtime and shimmer
  const voice = new OpenAIRealtimeVoice({
    apiKey: process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY,
    model: "gpt-4o-realtime",   // <-- your target realtime model
    speaker: "shimmer",         // <-- default speaker for all speech
  });

  // (Optional) tweak server VAD / other session options
  voice.updateSession?.({
    turn_detection: {
      type: "server_vad",
      threshold: 0.6,
      silence_duration_ms: 1200,
    },
  });

  // 2. Connect to OpenAI Realtime
  await voice.connect();

  // 3. Handle outgoing audio and transcribed text
  voice.on("speaker", ({ audio }) => {
    // audio is Int16Array PCM
    playAudio(audio);
  });

  voice.on("writing", ({ text, role }) => {
    console.log(`${role}: ${text}`);
  });

  // 4. Start the conversation with shimmer
  await voice.speak("Hi, I'm shimmer. How can I help you?");

  // 5. Stream microphone audio to the model for full STS
  const micStream = getMicrophoneStream();
  await voice.send(micStream);

  // When you’re done, remember to close the connection:
  // await voice.close();
}

main().catch(console.error);
```

This gives you full speech‑to‑speech:

- Model: `gpt-4o-realtime`
- Default speaker: `shimmer`
- Incoming audio from mic → model
- Outgoing audio from model → `playAudio(audio)`

---

### 3. Using `OpenAIRealtimeVoice` with an Agent

If you want this attached to a Mastra `Agent`:

```ts
import { Agent } from "@mastra/core/agent";
import { OpenAIRealtimeVoice } from "@mastra/voice-openai-realtime";
import { playAudio, getMicrophoneStream } from "@mastra/node-audio";

async function main() {
  const agent = new Agent({
    id: "realtime-agent",
    name: "Realtime Voice Agent",
    instructions:
      "You are a helpful assistant with real-time voice capabilities.",
    // Text model for general reasoning; voice provider handles realtime audio
    model: "openai/gpt-4o",
    voice: new OpenAIRealtimeVoice({
      apiKey: process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY,
      model: "gpt-4o-realtime",
      speaker: "shimmer",
    }),
  });

  await agent.voice.connect();

  agent.voice.on("speaker", ({ audio }) => {
    playAudio(audio);
  });

  agent.voice.on("writing", ({ role, text }) => {
    console.log(`${role}: ${text}`);
  });

  await agent.voice.speak("Hi, I'm shimmer running on gpt-4o-realtime. Ask me anything.");

  const micStream = getMicrophoneStream();
  await agent.voice.send(micStream);
}

main().catch(console.error);
```

