You can send the same Mastra traces to **both Langfuse and your OpenTelemetry backend simultaneously** by configuring a single observability config with **multiple exporters**: `LangfuseExporter` + `OtelExporter`.

Mastra explicitly supports “fan-out” to multiple exporters from one config; you do **not** need multiple configs for this.

---

## 1. Install the required packages

```bash
pnpm add @mastra/observability @mastra/langfuse@beta @mastra/otel-exporter@beta
# plus one OTLP protocol package depending on your OTEL backend, for example:
# HTTP/Protobuf (SigNoz, New Relic, Laminar, many collectors):
pnpm add @opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-proto
# or HTTP/JSON:
# pnpm add @opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-http
# or gRPC:
# pnpm add @opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-grpc @grpc/grpc-js
```

---

## 2. Example: Langfuse + generic OTEL collector

This sends traces to:

- Langfuse (via `LangfuseExporter`)
- Any OTEL-compatible backend (via `OtelExporter` with a `custom` OTLP endpoint)

```ts
// src/mastra/index.ts
import { Mastra } from "@mastra/core";
import {
  Observability,
  DefaultExporter,
  CloudExporter,
} from "@mastra/observability";
import { LangfuseExporter } from "@mastra/langfuse";
import { OtelExporter } from "@mastra/otel-exporter";

export const mastra = new Mastra({
  observability: new Observability({
    // Turn OFF the implicit default config since we're defining our own
    default: { enabled: false },

    configs: {
      production: {
        serviceName: "my-service",

        // One config, multiple exporters (fan-out)
        exporters: [
          // 1) Langfuse
          new LangfuseExporter({
            publicKey: process.env.LANGFUSE_PUBLIC_KEY!,
            secretKey: process.env.LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY!,
            baseUrl: process.env.LANGFUSE_BASE_URL, // e.g. https://cloud.langfuse.com
            realtime: process.env.NODE_ENV === "development",
            options: {
              environment: process.env.NODE_ENV,
            },
          }),

          // 2) OpenTelemetry backend (via your collector / vendor)
          new OtelExporter({
            provider: {
              custom: {
                endpoint:
                  process.env.OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT ??
                  "https://your-collector.example.com/v1/traces",
                protocol: "http/protobuf", // or 'http/json' | 'grpc'
                headers: {
                  "x-api-key": process.env.OTEL_API_KEY ?? "",
                },
              },
            },
          }),

          // Optional: keep Mastra Studio & Cloud
          new DefaultExporter(), // Mastra Studio (local)
          new CloudExporter(),   // Mastra Cloud (requires MASTRA_CLOUD_ACCESS_TOKEN)
        ],
      },
    },

    // Simple selector: always use the "production" config
    configSelector: () => "production",
  }),

  // your other Mastra config (agents, workflows, storage, etc.)
});
```

Key points:

- The **same trace** is exported to **all exporters** listed in `exporters: [...]`.
- You must set `default: { enabled: false }` when you define `configs`, otherwise the built-in default config “wins” and your custom one won’t be used.
- You can still add Studio/Cloud exporters alongside Langfuse and OTEL if you want.

---

## 3. Example: Langfuse + specific OTEL provider (e.g., SigNoz)

For convenience, Mastra’s OTEL exporter includes provider presets like `signoz`, `newrelic`, `dash0`, etc. Here’s Langfuse + SigNoz:

```ts
import { Mastra } from "@mastra/core";
import { Observability } from "@mastra/observability";
import { LangfuseExporter } from "@mastra/langfuse";
import { OtelExporter } from "@mastra/otel-exporter";

export const mastra = new Mastra({
  observability: new Observability({
    default: { enabled: false },

    configs: {
      otel_and_langfuse: {
        serviceName: "my-service",
        exporters: [
          new LangfuseExporter({
            publicKey: process.env.LANGFUSE_PUBLIC_KEY!,
            secretKey: process.env.LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY!,
            baseUrl: process.env.LANGFUSE_BASE_URL,
            realtime: process.env.NODE_ENV === "development",
          }),
          new OtelExporter({
            provider: {
              signoz: {
                apiKey: process.env.SIGNOZ_API_KEY!,
                region: "us", // or 'eu' | 'in'
                // endpoint: 'https://my-signoz.example.com', // for self-hosted
              },
            },
          }),
        ],
      },
    },

    configSelector: () => "otel_and_langfuse",
  }),
});
```

Swap `signoz` for `newrelic`, `dash0`, `laminar`, `traceloop`, or `custom` depending on your backend.

---

## 4. Optionally: Also use the OpenTelemetry Bridge

If you already have OTEL SDK + auto-instrumentation and want Mastra spans to:

- join your existing distributed traces, and
- still fan-out to Langfuse & OTEL,

you can combine the **OtelBridge** with exporters:

```ts
import { Mastra } from "@mastra/core";
import { Observability, DefaultExporter } from "@mastra/observability";
import { OtelBridge } from "@mastra/otel-bridge";
import { LangfuseExporter } from "@mastra/langfuse";
import { OtelExporter } from "@mastra/otel-exporter";

export const mastra = new Mastra({
  observability: new Observability({
    default: { enabled: false },
    configs: {
      default: {
        serviceName: "my-service",
        bridge: new OtelBridge(), // connects to existing OTEL context
        exporters: [
          new DefaultExporter(),
          new LangfuseExporter({
            publicKey: process.env.LANGFUSE_PUBLIC_KEY!,
            secretKey: process.env.LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY!,
          }),
          new OtelExporter({
            provider: {
              custom: {
                endpoint:
                  process.env.OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT ??
                  "http://localhost:4318/v1/traces",
                protocol: "http/protobuf",
              },
            },
          }),
        ],
      },
    },
    configSelector: () => "default",
  }),
});
```

In that setup:

- The **OTEL SDK** (your instrumentation file) decides where OTEL-native spans go.
- Mastra **also** ships the same trace to Langfuse and your backend directly via exporters.

---

## 5. How to choose between patterns

- **Just want “send once to Langfuse + OTEL”**:  
  Use **only exporters** (first examples). No OTEL bridge required.

- **Already have OTEL auto-instrumentation & distributed tracing** and want Mastra spans to be in the same trace graph:  
  Use **OtelBridge + exporters** (section 4).

In all cases, the rule from the docs applies:

> “A single config can send data to multiple exporters simultaneously.”

---

